@sourav-mazumder @Leemoonsoo There are two good reasons why Zeppelin should run each note as a separate Spark app instance.
1. Dependencies - each note may have different dependencies (expressed as %dep, as a spark package, etc.)
2. Scale - it is reasonable that each note has unique scale requirements; one might be memory-intensive, etc.

I don't think a per-user instance would address those concerns.

@Leemoonsoo how hard would it be to achieve that, and how can I help?

